    >>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
    False
    >>> portal.portal_quickinstaller.installProduct("openc.objectsfromlinks")
    'Installing text/web-intelligent mimetype and transform
Registered mimetype text/html-with-embeds
Registered transform html_to_embed
'
    >>> 'html_to_embed' in portal.portal_transforms.objectIds()
    True
    >>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
    True

If a page has a link to a flv it will add metadata in::
    
    >>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Test</h1><a href='%s/%s'>foo</a>" % ('/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), fid))
    >>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
    '<h1>Test</h1><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/myflv.flv" class="flv_w360h288v0">
 foo
</a>'

As it will for a SWF::

    >>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Test</h1><a href='%s/%s'>foo</a>" % ('/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), fidswf))
    >>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
    '<h1>Test</h1><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/myswf.swf" class="swf_w65h65v8">
 foo
</a>'


It will keep other HTML the same though::

    >>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Foo</h1><hr /><p>This is a thing</p><hr /><p>As is this!</p>")
    >>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
    '<h1>Foo</h1><hr /><p>This is a thing</p><hr /><p>As is this!</p>'

    >>> file.filename="a.out.bz2"

Now, if we link to it the SWF will still have its class but the bz2 will be unaltered::

    >>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Test</h1><a href='%s/%s'>foo</a><hr /><a href='%s/%s'>bar</a>" % ('/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), fidswf,'/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), bz2fid))
    >>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
    '<h1>Test</h1><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/myswf.swf" class="swf_w65h65v8">
 foo
</a><hr /><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/a.out.bz2">bar</a>'

If we uninstall the product again the mimetype and transform are gone::

    >>> portal.portal_quickinstaller.uninstallProducts(("openc.objectsfromlinks",))
    >>> 'html_to_embed' in portal.portal_transforms.objectIds()
    False
    >>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
    False


Changelog
=========

1.1
---

* Add hachoir to us as a fallback parser for things hexagonit's parser can't handle.  hachoir isn't as forgiving as hexagonit for SWF, so keep it in reserve.  Enables FLV support.
  [MatthewWilkes]

* Various bugfixes
  [MatthewWilkes]

1.0
---

* Initial version, includes portal transform and SWF metadata support.
  [MatthewWilkes]

>>> fileswf.filename="myswf.swf"

>>> self.folder[fid].setFile(file)

>>> fid in self.folder.objectIds()
True
>>> fidswf in self.folder.objectIds()
True

Now we can find metadata about this file:

>>> from openc.objectsfromlinks.interfaces import IMetadata
>>> m = IMetadata(self.folder[fid])
>>> m.width
360
>>> m.height
288

And about the SWF:

>>> m = IMetadata(self.folder[fidswf])
>>> m.width
65
>>> m.height
65

If we install the product into Plone we’ll get a text transform:

>>> 'html_to_embed' in portal.portal_transforms.objectIds()
False
>>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
False
>>> portal.portal_quickinstaller.installProduct("openc.objectsfromlinks")
'Installing text/web-intelligent mimetype and transform
Registered mimetype text/html-with-embeds
Registered transform html_to_embed
'
>>> 'html_to_embed' in portal.portal_transforms.objectIds()
True
>>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
True

If a page has a link to a flv it will add metadata in:

>>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Test</h1><a href='%s/%s'>foo</a>" % ('/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), fid))
>>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
'<h1>Test</h1><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/myflv.flv" class="flv_w360h288v0">
 foo
</a>'

As it will for a SWF:

>>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Test</h1><a href='%s/%s'>foo</a>" % ('/'.join(self.folder.getPhysicalPath()), fidswf))
>>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
'<h1>Test</h1><a href="/plone/Members/test_user_1_/myswf.swf" class="swf_w65h65v8">
 foo
</a>'

It will keep other HTML the same though:

>>> self.portal['front-page'].setText("<h1>Foo</h1><hr /><p>This is a thing</p><hr /><p>As is this!</p>")
>>> self.portal['front-page'].getText()
'<h1>Foo</h1><hr /><p>This is a thing</p><hr /><p>As is this!</p>'

If we uninstall the product again the mimetype and transform are gone:

>>> portal.portal_quickinstaller.uninstallProducts(("openc.objectsfromlinks",))
>>> 'html_to_embed' in portal.portal_transforms.objectIds()
False
>>> '<mimetype text/html-with-embeds>' in [`a` for a in portal.mimetypes_registry.mimetypes()]
False

Changelog

1.1

  • Add hachoir to us as a fallback parser for things hexagonit’s parser can’t handle. hachoir isn’t as forgiving as hexagonit for SWF, so keep it in reserve. Enables FLV support. [MatthewWilkes]
  • Various bugfixes [MatthewWilkes]

1.0

  • Initial version, includes portal transform and SWF metadata support. [MatthewWilkes]
